Detailed Description

cvmx_dfm_reset_ctl

Specify the RSL base addresses for the block

Notes: DDR3RST - DDR3 DRAM parts have a new RESET# pin that wasn't present in DDR2 parts. The DDR3RST CSR field controls the assertion of the new 6xxx pin that attaches to RESET#. When DDR3RST is set, 6xxx asserts RESET#. When DDR3RST is clear, 6xxx de-asserts RESET#.

DDR3RST is set on a cold reset. Warm and soft chip resets do not affect the DDR3RST value. Outside of cold reset, only software CSR writes change the DDR3RST value.
